cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV. 

The paper presents a modular approach for learning policies for navigation over long planning horizons from language input, which involves multiple levels of hierarchy and imitation learning followed by reinforcement learning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) for the use of machine learning techniques, cs.RO (Robotics) for the focus on navigation and control, cs.CL (Computation and Language) for the use of language input, cs.LG (Machine Learning) for the use of imitation learning and reinforcement learning, and cs.CV (Computer Vision) for the use of visual input in the House3D environment.
